<paragraph id="8B9E0A5D671BE06DB39DFB7DFBB80BF6" blockId="24.[151,1111,1086,1185]" box="[151,1111,1159,1185]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">
Synonymized under 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB275FB7DFCAE0BF6" authority="(Burmeister, 1839)" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[383,833,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Anisochrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasina">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB275FB7DFD890BF6" box="[383,614,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">Anisochrysa prasina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB17EFB7DFCD60BF6" author="Burmeister, H. C. C." box="[628,825,1159,1185]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="757 - 1050" refId="ref18271" refString="Burmeister, H. C. C. (1839) s. n. In: Handbuch der Entomologie. Zweiter Band. Besondere Entomologie. Zweite Abteilung. Kaukerfe. Gymnognatha. Zweite Ha ¨ lfte. Vulgo Neuroptera. T. C. F. Enslin, Berlin, pp. 757 - 1050." type="book chapter" year="1839">Burmeister, 1839</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB063FB7DFBBD0BF6" author="Aspock, H. &amp; Aspock, U. &amp; Holzel, H." box="[873,1106,1159,1185]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" refId="ref17836" refString="Aspock, H., Aspock, U. &amp; Holzel, H. (1980) Die Neuropteren Europas. Eine zusammenfassende Darstellung der Systematik, Okologie und Chorologie der Neuropteroidea (Megaloptera, Raphidioptera, Planipennia) Europas. Vols. 1. &amp; 2. Goecke and Evers, Krefeld, 495 pp. &amp; 355 pp." type="book" year="1980">
Aspöck 
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB0CCFB72FC110BF6" box="[966,1022,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">et al.</emphasis>
(1980)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33B59D6671BE06DB39DFB35FF1108EE" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9E0A5D671BE06DB39DFB35FC1B097A" blockId="24.[151,1437,1231,1977]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB39DFB35FE690BBE" author="Legrand, J. &amp; Tauber, C. A. &amp; Albuquerque, G. S. &amp; Tauber, M. J." box="[151,390,1231,1257]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="103 - 183" refId="ref18968" refString="Legrand, J., Tauber, C. A., Albuquerque, G. S. &amp; Tauber, M. J. (2008) Navas &quot; type and non-type specimens of Chrysopidae in the MNHN, Paris [Neuroptera]. Revue Francaise d &quot; Entomologie, 30, 103 - 183." type="journal article" year="2008">
Legrand 
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB3F6FB2AFEDB0BBE" box="[252,308,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
designated the type specimen at the Natural History Museum in Paris (MNHN) as 
<typeStatus id="549AB4FF671BE06DB625FB35FA760BBE" box="[1327,1433,1231,1257]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The male type specimen had been collected in the region of Smyrne (
<collectingRegion id="49E5C4BF671BE06DB093FB09FC360A59" box="[921,985,1267,1294]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">Izmir</collectingRegion>
) in western 
<collectingCountry id="F3364ACD671BE06DB76BFB09FB5D0A5A" box="[1121,1202,1267,1293]" name="Turkey" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<date id="FF9F2C9D671BE06DB7B7FB09FABB0A5A" box="[1213,1364,1267,1294]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" value="1912-05-14">14 May 1912</date>
, by G. de Kerville. The original description by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB15DFAEDFD1E0A65" author="Navas, L." box="[599,753,1303,1330]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="111 - 120" refId="ref19553" refString="Navas, L. (1926) Insecta orientalia. Memorie dell'Accademia Pontifica dei Nuovi Lincei, Rome, IV Series, 9, 111 - 120." type="journal article" year="1926">Navás (1926)</bibRefCitation>
, featuring the yellow vertex, could apply to several prasinoid species, but an inspection of the male type in Paris by PD showed 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB087FAC1FBE70A02" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1926" box="[909,1032,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB087FAC1FBE70A02" box="[909,1032,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">A. vernalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be closest to Ap1. The male still has a yellow vertex. This specimen does not have furwings, which excludes Ap2, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB749FAA5FB550A2E" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1091,1210,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Anisochrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasina">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB749FAA5FB550A2E" box="[1091,1210,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">A. prasina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB7F1FAA5FA7A0A2E" box="[1275,1429,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apertochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benedictae">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB7F1FAA5FA7A0A2E" box="[1275,1429,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">A. benedictae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examples of Ap1 were found in 2012 on the Greek island of Samos, barely 
<quantity id="4CD9A7B8671BE06DB0DFFA79FBF40ACA" box="[981,1051,1411,1437]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" unit="km" value="60.0">60 km</quantity>
from 
<collectingRegion id="49E5C4BF671BE06DB756FA79FB760ACA" box="[1116,1177,1411,1437]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">Izmir</collectingRegion>
(PD, unpublished). So, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB39DFA5DFEFE0A96" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1926" box="[151,273,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB39DFA5DFEFE0A96" box="[151,273,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">A. vernalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to correspond to Ap1. However, there is an older type specimen described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB7C1FA5DFA8C0A96" author="Navas, L." box="[1227,1379,1447,1473]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="211 - 216" refId="ref19524" refString="Navas, L. (1914) Quelques Nevropteres recueillis par le Dr. Malcolm Burr en Transcaucasie. Revue Russe d'Entomologie, 14, 211 - 216." type="journal article" year="1914">Navás (1914)</bibRefCitation>
with yellowish vertex (
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB26BFA31FD360AB2" authority="Navas, 1914" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1914" box="[353,729,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB26BFA31FDAA0AB2" box="[353,581,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">Chrysopa caucasica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB146FA31FD360AB2" author="Navas, L." box="[588,729,1483,1509]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="211 - 216" refId="ref19524" refString="Navas, L. (1914) Quelques Nevropteres recueillis par le Dr. Malcolm Burr en Transcaucasie. Revue Russe d'Entomologie, 14, 211 - 216." type="journal article" year="1914">Navás, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) from Transcaucasia. It is a female and the original description and an examination of the specimen at the museum in Paris were inadequate for conclusive identification. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB39DF9EEFEC7097A" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1914" box="[151,296,1556,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB39DF9EEFEC7097A" box="[151,296,1556,1582]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">C. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, older than 
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB2A4F9EEFDC0097A" box="[430,559,1555,1582]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB2A4F9EEFDC4097A" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1926" box="[430,555,1555,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">C. vernalis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
could instead be Ap1 - or possibly Ap2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9E0A5D671BE06DB3CDF9CDFF1108EE" blockId="24.[151,1437,1231,1977]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">
Earlier than either of the two species above, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB1B1F9CDFCBE0906" author="Navas, L." box="[699,849,1591,1617]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="204 - 211" refId="ref19444" refString="Navas, L. (1911) Notas entomologicas. [2 nd series]. 3. Excursiones por los alrededores de Granada. Boletin de la Sociedad Aragonesa de Ciencias Naturales, 10, 204 - 211." type="journal article" year="1911">Navás (1911)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB0C1F9C2FB350906" box="[971,1242,1591,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Anisochrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="prasina" variety="amabilis">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB0C1F9C2FBAD0906" box="[971,1090,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">C. prasina</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB770F9CDFB350906" box="[1146,1242,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">amabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with red sutures below the antennae. The description would fit Ap1, with two reddish-brown longitudinal bands (“linea arcuate rubra ante antennas”). However, Navás did not mention a yellow vertex, and his 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB0E3F97AFB9509CE" box="[1001,1146,1663,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Anisochrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="prasina" variety="amabilis">
var. 
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB710F985FB9509CE" box="[1050,1146,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">amabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
better fits the description of Ap2, which also occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="F3364ACD671BE06DB2E4F959FDC109EA" box="[494,558,1699,1725]" name="Spain" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode id="ED309298671BE06DB14BF959FDB809EA" box="[577,599,1699,1725]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">R</collectionCode>
. Alcalá Herrera &amp; F. Ruano, unpublished information). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB7D6F959FA9709EA" author="Navas, L." box="[1244,1400,1699,1725]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="204 - 211" refId="ref19444" refString="Navas, L. (1911) Notas entomologicas. [2 nd series]. 3. Excursiones por los alrededores de Granada. Boletin de la Sociedad Aragonesa de Ciencias Naturales, 10, 204 - 211." type="journal article" year="1911">Navás (1911)</bibRefCitation>
, in his original description, even mentioned that the 
<typeStatus id="549AB4FF671BE06DB1D1F932FCE409B5" box="[731,779,1736,1762]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">type</typeStatus>
specimen looked like “similis 
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB776F93DFB0109B6" box="[1148,1262,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">adspersae</emphasis>
(sic.) Wesm.”. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB239F911FE440852" box="[307,427,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Anisochrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspersa">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB239F911FE440852" box="[307,427,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">A. aspersa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also is a good candidate for assignment to Ap2 (see below). Ap1 was recently found in large numbers near Granada, 
<collectingCountry id="F3364ACD671BE06DB2EAF8F5FDCF087E" box="[480,544,1807,1833]" name="Spain" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode id="ED309298671BE06DB13AF8F5FDA9087E" box="[560,582,1807,1833]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">R</collectionCode>
. Alcalá Herrera &amp; F. Ruano, unpublished information), and Navás may have seen and described several specimens of Ap1 as new varieties of either 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB0C6F8C9FB78081A" baseAuthorityName="Principi" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[972,1175,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasina">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB0C6F8C9FB78081A" box="[972,1175,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">Chrysopa prasina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB7CAF8CEFAAE081A" baseAuthorityName="Navas" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[1216,1345,1844,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Dichochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mariana">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB7CAF8CEFAAE081A" box="[1216,1345,1844,1870]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">C. mariana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. With a molecular sequencing approach now being applied to older 
<typeStatus id="549AB4FF671BE06DB04CF8A2FC990825" box="[838,886,1880,1906]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">type</typeStatus>
specimens (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB077AC671BE06DB70FF8ADFB3F0825" author="Price, B. W. &amp; Henry, C. S. &amp; Hall, A. &amp; Mochizuki, A. &amp; Duelli, P. &amp; Brooks, S. J." box="[1029,1232,1879,1906]" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref20017" refString="Price, B. W., Henry, C. S., Hall, A., Mochizuki, A., Duelli, P. &amp; Brooks, S. J. (2015) Singing from the grave: DNA from a 180 year old type specimen confirms the identity of Chrysoperla carnea (Stephens). PLoS ONE, 10, 1 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0121127" type="journal article" year="2015">
Price 
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB743F8A2FB6B0826" box="[1097,1156,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">et al.</emphasis>
, 2015
</bibRefCitation>
), both 
<taxonomicName id="4C2171DE671BE06DB62BF8ADFA730826" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1926" box="[1313,1436,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Chrysopa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vernalis">
<emphasis id="B955D64F671BE06DB62BF8ADFA730826" box="[1313,1436,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="85">A. vernalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Ap1 may eventually be established as junior synonyms to one of the earlier described prasinoid species or varieties.
</paragraph>
